{"search_data": "HaryanaSaksham Yuva Scheme in Haryana for Unemployed YouthThe state government launched the Saksham Yuva Scheme in November 2016 and the implementation begin from December 2016. The state government had decided to invest Rs 324 crore for this scheme for post graduates but the inclusion of unemployed graduates will require more budget.Saksham Yuva SchemeUnder the Saksham Yuva scheme, the state government provides employment opportunities to the unemployed youth by placing them in different government departments. The permanent state residents who have completed their graduation or post graduation from University of Delhi, Chandigarh or any recognized university in Haryana are eligible for the scheme.To be eligible for the scheme, the total annual income of the household should not exceed Rs. 3 Lakh and the candidate should not be working anywhere in either private or public sector company.Apply Online for Saksham Yuva SchemeThe applications for the Saksham Yuva Scheme are being invited through online modes. The candidates can register themselves under the Saksham Yuva Scheme through the official website at hreyahs.gov.in.More details about the scheme can be downloaded in the PDF format from the link below. Haryana Saksham Yuva Scheme Details.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}